&lt;P class=MsoNormal auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: mso-margin-top-alt: auto? 0pt; 0in justify; TEXT-ALIGN: **Oompa-Loompa**?MARGIN:&gt;&lt;SPAN **Oompa-Loompa**?FONT-SIZE: #cccccc; FONT-FAMILY: COLOR: Roman?? 12pt; ?Times New&gt;7)&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; &lt;B&gt;Discipline stacking and timer issues.&lt;/B&gt;&amp;nbsp; A lot of monks feel throw stone should not be on the same timer as phantom lull and planes walk should not be with healing will.&amp;nbsp; Whirlwind also has a very long reuse timer and its tied to stonestance and earth walk, which are some life saving disciplines while pulling.&amp;nbsp; &lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;FONT color=#ff0000&gt;&lt;SPAN **Oompa-Loompa**?FONT-SIZE: FONT-FAMILY: COLOR: Roman?? 12pt; ?Times New red;&gt;&lt;SPAN FONT-FAMILY: COLOR: Roman?? 12pt; ?Times New **SMURF**?FONT-SIZE: red;&gt;&lt;FONT color=#ff0000&gt;&lt;SPAN **Oompa-Loompa**?FONT-SIZE: FONT-FAMILY: COLOR: Roman?? 12pt; ?Times New red;&gt;&lt;FONT color=#ff0000&gt;&lt;SPAN FONT-FAMILY: COLOR: Roman?? 12pt; ?Times New **SMURF**?FONT-SIZE: red;&gt;&lt;FONT color=#ff0000&gt;Currently being discussed&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P class=MsoNormal auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: mso-margin-top-alt: auto? 0pt; 0in justify; TEXT-ALIGN: **Oompa-Loompa**?MARGIN:&gt;&lt;SPAN **Oompa-Loompa**?FONT-SIZE: #cccccc; FONT-FAMILY: COLOR: Roman?? 12pt; ?Times New&gt;8)&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;Add more benifits for staying under weight &lt;SPAN Gothic?? ?Century **SMURF**?mso-bidi-font-family:&gt;&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;FONT color=#ff0000&gt;&lt;SPAN red; mso-bidi-font-family: Gothic?? ?Century **SMURF**?COLOR:&gt;&lt;SPAN #cccccc; Verdana? FONT-FAMILY: **SMURF**?COLOR:&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;This item was added to the list with the 10/8/04 update, there isn't any feedback on this item yet.&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;FONT color=#ff0000&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P class=MsoNormal 0in **SMURF**?MARGIN: 0pt 0.5in?&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN **Oompa-Loompa**?FONT-SIZE: #cccccc; FONT-FAMILY: COLOR: Roman?? 12pt; ?Times New&gt;&lt;STRONG&gt;Suggested benifits - &lt;/STRONG&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;UL&gt;&#xD;
&lt;LI&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV class=MsoNormal auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: mso-margin-top-alt: auto? 0pt; 0in justify; TEXT-ALIGN: **Oompa-Loompa**?MARGIN:&gt;&lt;SPAN **Oompa-Loompa**?FONT-SIZE: #cccccc; FONT-FAMILY: COLOR: Roman?? 12pt; ?Times New&gt;Innate increase to runspeed&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;LI&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV class=MsoNormal auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: mso-margin-top-alt: auto? 0pt; 0in justify; TEXT-ALIGN: **Oompa-Loompa**?MARGIN:&gt;&lt;SPAN **Oompa-Loompa**?FONT-SIZE: #cccccc; FONT-FAMILY: COLOR: Roman?? 12pt; ?Times New&gt;Avoidance &lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;LI&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV class=MsoNormal auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: mso-margin-top-alt: auto? 0pt; 0in justify; TEXT-ALIGN: **Oompa-Loompa**?MARGIN:&gt;&lt;SPAN **Oompa-Loompa**?FONT-SIZE: #cccccc; FONT-FAMILY: COLOR: Roman?? 12pt; ?Times New&gt;Attack speed. &lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&lt;/LI&gt;&lt;/UL&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P class=MsoNormal auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: mso-margin-top-alt: auto? 0pt; 0in justify; TEXT-ALIGN: **Oompa-Loompa**?MARGIN:&gt;&lt;SPAN **Oompa-Loompa**?FONT-SIZE: #cccccc; FONT-FAMILY: COLOR: Roman?? 12pt; ?Times New&gt;9)&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; &lt;B&gt;Purify Body refresh timer.&lt;/B&gt; Purify Soul had its refresh timer reduced many patches ago. Purify Body has not had its refresh timer touched. The cleric and monk version cost the same amount of AA and the same amount of AA to upgrade through the PoP upgrade. The refresh timers should be equal.&amp;nbsp; &lt;FONT color=#ff0000&gt;Notes from Rashere below - &lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P class=MsoNormal auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: mso-margin-top-alt: auto? 0pt; 0in justify; TEXT-ALIGN: **Oompa-Loompa**?MARGIN:&gt;&lt;SPAN **Oompa-Loompa**?FONT-SIZE: #cccccc; FONT-FAMILY: COLOR: Roman?? 12pt; ?Times New&gt;&lt;FONT color=#ff0000&gt;Ok, this is a bit odd…so bear with me.&amp;nbsp; There is nothing wrong with two different classes having a similar ability and one class being able to use it more often than another.&amp;nbsp; In some cases, it’s very appropriate.&amp;nbsp; For the purify abilities specifically, it makes perfect sense that a cleric, a class all about healing and cleansing, can purify themselves more often than a monk can.&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P class=MsoNormal auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: mso-margin-top-alt: auto? 0pt; 0in justify; TEXT-ALIGN: **Oompa-Loompa**?MARGIN:&gt;&lt;SPAN **Oompa-Loompa**?FONT-SIZE: #cccccc; FONT-FAMILY: COLOR: Roman?? 12pt; ?Times New&gt;&lt;FONT color=#ff0000&gt;That being said, I do feel that a 72 minute reuse on Purify Body is too long so I’m going to lower it to half an hour.&amp;nbsp; This is the same reuse as the cleric ability.&amp;nbsp; I want to be very clear, though, that I’m not lowering it because clerics have a similar ability with a different reuse timer.&amp;nbsp; If that was the only reason to do it, I wouldn’t be lowering it at all.&amp;nbsp; I’m lowering it because I feel the reuse on the monk ability is too long.&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P class=MsoNormal auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: mso-margin-top-alt: auto? 0pt; 0in justify; TEXT-ALIGN: **Oompa-Loompa**?MARGIN:&gt;&lt;SPAN **Oompa-Loompa**?FONT-SIZE: #cccccc; FONT-FAMILY: COLOR: Roman?? 12pt; ?Times New&gt;10) &amp;nbsp;&lt;B&gt;Ranged item stats.&lt;/B&gt;&amp;nbsp; Monks have to lose stats while pulling due to losing their range item.&amp;nbsp; Some suggestions have been made of using only the ammo slot to throw from.&amp;nbsp; Putting more monk throw able items in game with good stats with a drop rate which makes them a viable pulling tool instead of a rare stat item.&amp;nbsp; More trade skill items with stats so they can be made and sold.&amp;nbsp; &lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;FONT color=#ff0000&gt;&lt;SPAN **Oompa-Loompa**?FONT-SIZE: FONT-FAMILY: COLOR: Roman?? 12pt; ?Times New red;&gt;&lt;SPAN FONT-FAMILY: COLOR: Roman?? 12pt; ?Times New **SMURF**?FONT-SIZE: red;&gt;&lt;FONT color=#ff0000&gt;&lt;SPAN **Oompa-Loompa**?FONT-SIZE: FONT-FAMILY: COLOR: Roman?? 12pt; ?Times New red;&gt;&lt;FONT color=#ff0000&gt;&lt;SPAN FONT-FAMILY: COLOR: Roman?? 12pt; ?Times New **SMURF**?FONT-SIZE: red;&gt;&lt;FONT color=#ff0000&gt;&lt;SPAN **Oompa-Loompa**?FONT-SIZE: FONT-FAMILY: COLOR: Roman?? 12pt; ?Times New red;&gt;&lt;FONT color=#ff0000&gt;&lt;SPAN FONT-FAMILY: COLOR: Roman?? 12pt; ?Times New **SMURF**?FONT-SIZE: red;&gt;&lt;FONT color=#ff0000&gt;This is a revised item.&amp;nbsp; Passing the new information along.&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P class=MsoNormal auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: mso-margin-top-alt: auto? 0pt; 0in justify; TEXT-ALIGN: **Oompa-Loompa**?MARGIN:&gt;&lt;SPAN **Oompa-Loompa**?FONT-SIZE: FONT-FAMILY: COLOR: Roman?? 12pt; ?Times New red;&gt;&lt;SPAN FONT-FAMILY: COLOR: Roman?? 12pt; ?Times New **SMURF**?FONT-SIZE: red;&gt;&lt;SPAN **Oompa-Loompa**?FONT-SIZE: FONT-FAMILY: COLOR: Roman?? 12pt; ?Times New red;&gt;&lt;SPAN FONT-FAMILY: COLOR: Roman?? 12pt; ?Times New **SMURF**?FONT-SIZE: red;&gt;&lt;SPAN **Oompa-Loompa**?FONT-SIZE: FONT-FAMILY: COLOR: Roman?? 12pt; ?Times New red;&gt;&lt;SPAN FONT-FAMILY: COLOR: Roman?? 12pt; ?Times New **SMURF**?FONT-SIZE: red;&gt;Propose Solution: To &lt;SPAN&gt;insure that the ammo slot is used as the primary sorce of expendeture of thrown items.&amp;nbsp; With this, place throwing weapons in the game with appropriate stats to be used in the range slot.&amp;nbsp; The ammo should not have to be the same as the thrown weapon and the highest range should be used for distance.&amp;nbsp; These items used for stats should be no-drop and level required to prevent tweeking.&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;</description>
